// ch06 scalar table and elsewhere assume ordinary C++ `const`-qualified
// local variables work (e.g. a `const int x = 5;` is unremarkable real
// C++), same as `const` before a reference type (`const T&`) or a
// pointer type (`const T*`). Originally written as a known failure
// (found while probing whether a closure capturing a genuinely
// `const`-qualified outer variable by reference would be treated as a
// shared, not mutable, reference capture for ch05 §5.15's
// thread-shareable structural derivation) -- confirmed fixed on
// re-verification, renamed from
// `const_qualified_local_variable_is_not_yet_supported.scpp` to match.
int main() {
    const int x = 5;
    return x;
}
